nodes.bodyText:
Please don't use realistic-looking data here. I know it's obvious to you that it's just your home address (or whatever it is), but you're setting up some future developer or security person to have a panic attack.
For addresses, I like "123 MAIN ST, APT 456, PODUNK, IA, 12345" or something along those lines. Visually, it's obvious to anyone that it didn't come from real data.

nodes.bodyText: WTG!

What do ACOs want to do with these two fields? If we only add them here (as opposed to also adding them to "BeneficiariesHistory" AND backfilling/updating the data for it) then we'll only have them for a bene's most recent/current MBI -- we won't be able to use or return them for historical MBIs.
Added to beneficiary history as well.
Same as above: lean more towards non-realistic data.
